00:01:32,640 --> 00:01:35,040
=Love Again=

2
00:01:35,330 --> 00:01:38,140
=Episode 16=

3
00:01:43,960 --> 00:01:44,480
Liu.

4
00:01:45,090 --> 00:01:45,990
Thanks for helping out.

5
00:01:46,370 --> 00:01:47,320
Thank you so much.

6
00:01:47,480 --> 00:01:48,350
Don't worry about it.

7
00:01:49,090 --> 00:01:49,560
Hello?

8
00:01:50,370 --> 00:01:50,680
Hello?

9
00:01:51,120 --> 00:01:51,680
Chu!

10
00:01:52,090 --> 00:01:53,290
We had an agreement.

11
00:01:53,530 --> 00:01:55,680
We booked the auditorium for the day!

12
00:01:56,650 --> 00:01:57,960
Tell the business school

13
00:01:57,960 --> 00:01:59,250
to figure something out.

14
00:02:00,120 --> 00:02:01,480
I need to go. We're rehearsing.

15
00:02:01,480 --> 00:02:02,530
I'm hanging up.

16
00:02:03,010 --> 00:02:04,800
- Here.
- This handwriting is beautiful.

17
00:02:04,800 --> 00:02:06,360
I copied the lyrics last night myself.

18
00:02:06,930 --> 00:02:08,190
What time will Ms. Nie be here?

19
00:02:08,730 --> 00:02:09,810
We agreed on 2 PM.

20
00:02:10,320 --> 00:02:11,760
I'll go meet her at the front gate.

21
00:02:12,040 --> 00:02:12,730
All right.

22
00:02:13,120 --> 00:02:15,880
Attention, everyone. Quiet, please.

23
00:02:16,840 --> 00:02:19,720
Our literary consultant,
Ms. Nie, will be here

24
00:02:19,930 --> 00:02:21,280
this afternoon.

25
00:02:22,120 --> 00:02:23,610
Let's put on our best performance.

26
00:02:24,000 --> 00:02:25,210
Sing with skill,

27
00:02:25,490 --> 00:02:27,120
sing with spirit!

28
00:02:27,280 --> 00:02:28,160
All right!

29
00:02:30,120 --> 00:02:32,560
Shen, you wrote the lyrics yourself?

30
00:02:33,050 --> 00:02:34,160
I hand-copied them myself.

31
00:02:35,840 --> 00:02:37,250
That makes them even more precious.

32
00:02:44,090 --> 00:02:45,330
Enough.

33
00:02:45,330 --> 00:02:46,610
Ms. Peng, you're joining us today

34
00:02:46,610 --> 00:02:47,560
too?

35
00:02:48,490 --> 00:02:48,960
Yes.

36
00:02:49,050 --> 00:02:49,880
Let me tell you,

37
00:02:51,000 --> 00:02:52,060
if it weren't for Ms. Peng,

38
00:02:52,490 --> 00:02:53,400
there's no way

39
00:02:53,400 --> 00:02:55,810
I could've handled cooking
for over 30 people on my own.

40
00:02:56,530 --> 00:02:58,490
And she enjoys singing too.

41
00:02:58,490 --> 00:02:59,370
So she's joining us.

42
00:02:59,720 --> 00:03:00,490
I didn't do much.

43
00:03:01,250 --> 00:03:03,120
Ms. Peng, you look beautiful today.

44
00:03:03,770 --> 00:03:04,560
You're too kind.

45
00:03:04,650 --> 00:03:06,560
You do look beautiful.

46
00:03:06,680 --> 00:03:10,119
- The fabric looks lovely.
- The color's nice too.

47
00:03:10,120 --> 00:03:11,650
Of course. It cost 580.

48
00:03:12,880 --> 00:03:14,810
580? Peng Yulan!

49
00:03:14,840 --> 00:03:15,490
You...

50
00:03:16,050 --> 00:03:17,880
You certainly didn't hold back.

51
00:03:24,000 --> 00:03:25,220
Your lipstick's a little faded.

52
00:03:26,440 --> 00:03:27,050
Is it?

53
00:03:27,160 --> 00:03:28,490
Yes. Check in the mirror.

54
00:03:30,440 --> 00:03:32,120
Did you bring your lipstick?

55
00:03:32,650 --> 00:03:33,000
No.

56
00:03:33,210 --> 00:03:34,120
I figured as much.

57
00:03:36,770 --> 00:03:37,439
Look what I have.

58
00:03:37,440 --> 00:03:37,720
Here.

59
00:03:38,280 --> 00:03:38,750
Open wide.

60
00:03:40,000 --> 00:03:40,530
Fine.

61
00:03:45,120 --> 00:03:46,610
Don't move those lips.

62
00:03:48,440 --> 00:03:49,000
I want to see.

63
00:03:54,680 --> 00:03:56,279
Take a look. See if that's good.

64
00:03:56,280 --> 00:03:57,370
I don't want them too red.

65
00:03:57,610 --> 00:03:59,490
Oh, that's not a problem.

66
00:03:59,530 --> 00:04:00,840
Red lips make a fair lady.

67
00:04:03,280 --> 00:04:04,210
If you say so.

68
00:04:05,490 --> 00:04:05,910
Oh, right.

69
00:04:06,370 --> 00:04:07,960
When we get there,

70
00:04:08,810 --> 00:04:10,050
we'll bring the stuff in first.

71
00:04:10,250 --> 00:04:11,630
You hold off making your entrance.

72
00:04:12,210 --> 00:04:13,720
Don't come in until I call you.

73
00:04:16,720 --> 00:04:17,740
We'll bring the things in.

74
00:04:17,810 --> 00:04:19,220
You just bring your beautiful looks.

75
00:04:21,560 --> 00:04:22,170
Oh, you!

76
00:04:23,490 --> 00:04:25,560
Hey! Why are you grinning too?

77
00:04:25,560 --> 00:04:25,810
I...

78
00:04:25,810 --> 00:04:26,520
Don't laugh.

79
00:04:29,370 --> 00:04:35,930
♪I long to pluck one and wear it,♪

80
00:04:35,930 --> 00:04:48,930
♪but I fear it won't bloom next year.♪

81
00:04:51,000 --> 00:04:51,610
Excellent.

82
00:04:53,250 --> 00:04:54,400
We're getting into the zone.

83
00:04:54,760 --> 00:04:57,640
This afternoon,
our literary consultant, Ms. Nie,

84
00:04:57,930 --> 00:04:59,290
will be here in person.

85
00:04:59,610 --> 00:05:00,170
Let's

86
00:05:00,850 --> 00:05:01,860
keep up our performance.

87
00:05:02,370 --> 00:05:02,760
All right?

88
00:05:03,080 --> 00:05:03,810
Yes.

89
00:05:04,520 --> 00:05:05,610
Also,

90
00:05:06,410 --> 00:05:07,290
we've prepared lunch

91
00:05:07,370 --> 00:05:08,930
for our choir

92
00:05:09,120 --> 00:05:10,320
today.

93
00:05:10,640 --> 00:05:12,170
Great!

94
00:05:12,640 --> 00:05:13,910
I hope you brought your appetite.

95
00:05:14,120 --> 00:05:14,810
Yes.

96
00:05:15,640 --> 00:05:17,170
We're here, everyone!

97
00:05:17,320 --> 00:05:18,810
We brought lunch!

98
00:05:19,170 --> 00:05:20,440
We brought the clothes!

99
00:05:21,120 --> 00:05:22,320
We brought steamed buns!

100
00:05:22,560 --> 00:05:24,730
Freshly steamed meat buns!
Lunch is served!

101
00:05:24,810 --> 00:05:26,760
Come and get them! Plenty for everyone!

102
00:05:27,930 --> 00:05:28,640
Let's eat.

103
00:05:28,970 --> 00:05:29,850
Have another.

104
00:05:31,320 --> 00:05:31,880
All right.

105
00:05:32,200 --> 00:05:32,680
Eat up.

106
00:05:32,680 --> 00:05:33,760
I love steamed buns.

107
00:05:33,760 --> 00:05:34,490
Have a bun.

108
00:05:34,850 --> 00:05:35,510
Just half please.

109
00:05:36,200 --> 00:05:36,850
The bun's good.

110
00:05:37,200 --> 00:05:38,640
Tasty. The filling's great.

111
00:05:38,810 --> 00:05:39,680
Eat up!

112
00:05:40,120 --> 00:05:41,760
Eat up! There's enough to go around!

113
00:05:42,250 --> 00:05:42,810
Baoqin!

114
00:05:43,320 --> 00:05:44,410
Thank you and Liu so much

115
00:05:44,640 --> 00:05:45,729
for preparing all of this.

116
00:05:45,730 --> 00:05:47,410
You've prepared a feast for us.

117
00:05:47,410 --> 00:05:49,120
Oh, don't be so courteous!
We're a family!

118
00:05:50,550 --> 00:05:51,199
It's delicious.

119
00:05:51,200 --> 00:05:52,620
Liu and I can't take all the credit.

120
00:05:53,050 --> 00:05:54,200
My good friend, Peng Yulan,

121
00:05:54,640 --> 00:05:56,760
helped us make the steamed buns!

122
00:05:58,080 --> 00:05:59,370
- Who's Peng Yulan?
- Peng Yulan.

123
00:05:59,490 --> 00:06:00,560
She's my best friend.

124
00:06:00,810 --> 00:06:01,440
Peng Yulan!

125
00:06:01,930 --> 00:06:03,640
There's definitely more to Peng Yulan.

126
00:06:03,930 --> 00:06:05,560
She's our belle of the factory!

127
00:06:06,080 --> 00:06:06,930
She prepared

128
00:06:07,120 --> 00:06:08,000
the filling

129
00:06:08,250 --> 00:06:09,640
in the buns herself.

130
00:06:09,810 --> 00:06:10,930
We have to thank her, then.

131
00:06:11,120 --> 00:06:11,850
Peng Yulan!

132
00:06:12,200 --> 00:06:13,440
Where are you?

133
00:06:15,200 --> 00:06:16,610
Everyone wants to meet you.

134
00:06:16,850 --> 00:06:18,080
We're all waiting for you.

135
00:06:25,560 --> 00:06:27,250
Peng Yulan is here!

136
00:06:27,610 --> 00:06:28,490
Look, everybody!

137
00:06:29,250 --> 00:06:30,290
There she comes!

138
00:06:34,610 --> 00:06:35,760
Where were you?

139
00:06:36,000 --> 00:06:36,760
I was just outside.

140
00:06:37,370 --> 00:06:40,490
Professor Shen wanted
to thank you in person.

141
00:06:40,850 --> 00:06:41,440
Yes.

142
00:06:41,440 --> 00:06:42,290
You're welcome.

143
00:06:43,730 --> 00:06:44,680
Thank you, Peng.

144
00:06:45,120 --> 00:06:46,470
Have you eaten? You should join us.

145
00:06:46,850 --> 00:06:47,680
I already ate.

146
00:06:47,680 --> 00:06:48,290
All right.

147
00:06:48,490 --> 00:06:49,810
Thank you so much, Peng,

148
00:06:50,290 --> 00:06:51,880
for preparing lunch for all of us.

149
00:06:52,320 --> 00:06:53,640
It wasn't much.

150
00:06:53,680 --> 00:06:54,250
Sit down.

151
00:06:54,730 --> 00:06:55,050
Sit.

152
00:06:55,440 --> 00:06:55,760
Sit.

153
00:07:00,520 --> 00:07:01,850
Attention, everyone!

154
00:07:02,370 --> 00:07:03,970
Attention, please!

155
00:07:05,050 --> 00:07:07,760
The belle of the factory cooked for us!

156
00:07:07,970 --> 00:07:09,520
What about it?

157
00:07:10,370 --> 00:07:12,680
We're honored!

158
00:07:14,410 --> 00:07:17,880
Do you mean
the blower factory on Liuye Street?

159
00:07:17,880 --> 00:07:18,830
Yes, that's our factory!

160
00:07:19,320 --> 00:07:20,910
There's someone
named Hu Di there, right?

161
00:07:21,680 --> 00:07:23,050
Hu Di is our factory director.

162
00:07:23,050 --> 00:07:23,560
Yes.

163
00:07:23,760 --> 00:07:24,760
He's my cousin!

164
00:07:27,200 --> 00:07:29,080
How many cousins do you have?

165
00:07:32,170 --> 00:07:33,000
There they go again.

166
00:07:33,050 --> 00:07:34,170
Your jealousy is showing.

167
00:07:35,490 --> 00:07:36,080
Are you full?

168
00:07:36,370 --> 00:07:38,290
Have some chicken soup, Professor Shen.

169
00:07:38,810 --> 00:07:40,370
I already have some.

170
00:07:41,320 --> 00:07:43,930
I added goji berries
to the ginseng chicken soup.

171
00:07:44,200 --> 00:07:45,230
Good for boosting energy.

172
00:07:48,520 --> 00:07:49,680
Everyone!

173
00:07:50,000 --> 00:07:51,850
Professor Shen is having chicken soup!

174
00:07:54,170 --> 00:07:54,730
So what?

175
00:07:54,970 --> 00:07:57,370
The soup you're drinking is made
from the same chicken broth!

176
00:07:57,410 --> 00:07:58,490
It's fresh! Just as good!

177
00:07:58,730 --> 00:08:01,120
We're having the broth
from the chicken soup!

178
00:08:02,600 --> 00:08:04,479
- You guys can have some too.
- Greedy bugger.

179
00:08:04,480 --> 00:08:06,370
Professor Shen can't finish all of this.

180
00:08:06,410 --> 00:08:06,880
No, no...

181
00:08:07,410 --> 00:08:08,080
Have some!

182
00:08:08,370 --> 00:08:09,640
Give Gou some too.

183
00:08:09,640 --> 00:08:10,120
Come.

184
00:08:10,930 --> 00:08:11,680
Let's share.

185
00:08:11,680 --> 00:08:12,120
Right.

186
00:08:12,120 --> 00:08:12,970
You have some too.

187
00:08:12,970 --> 00:08:13,490
Here.

188
00:08:15,930 --> 00:08:17,680
She's got her eyes on Mr. Shen.

189
00:08:18,200 --> 00:08:18,930
Didn't expect

190
00:08:19,000 --> 00:08:20,880
Mr. Shen is still a heartthrob.

191
00:08:23,250 --> 00:08:25,320
Enjoy the food, everyone.

192
00:08:25,410 --> 00:08:27,170
I have good news to share.

193
00:08:27,320 --> 00:08:28,520
Tian and I

194
00:08:29,200 --> 00:08:30,680
are getting married

195
00:08:31,370 --> 00:08:32,380
on the 17th of this month!

196
00:08:33,490 --> 00:08:34,850
Everyone is invited!

197
00:08:35,100 --> 00:08:35,879
Make sure you come!

198
00:08:35,880 --> 00:08:37,080
I need to use the toilet.

199
00:08:37,370 --> 00:08:38,000
Go on.

200
00:08:38,000 --> 00:08:38,720
You guys carry on.

201
00:08:39,040 --> 00:08:39,710
Come back soon.

202
00:08:39,710 --> 00:08:41,200
We didn't hear anything about this!

203
00:08:41,200 --> 00:08:43,760
Prepare our wedding gifts!

204
00:08:44,800 --> 00:08:45,609
Don't listen to him!

205
00:08:45,610 --> 00:08:46,850
We don't need the gifts.

206
00:08:46,970 --> 00:08:48,400
We'd just love your attendance.

207
00:08:48,610 --> 00:08:49,970
It's not our first wedding anyway.

208
00:08:50,490 --> 00:08:52,210
It's her third and my second.

209
00:08:53,280 --> 00:08:55,610
No, no. My eighth and his tenth.

210
00:08:57,520 --> 00:08:59,370
You just love messing with them.

211
00:08:59,690 --> 00:09:01,500
My in-law's having an event
at his university.

212
00:09:01,920 --> 00:09:03,000
The whole family's over.

213
00:09:03,490 --> 00:09:04,310
It's a lively event.

214
00:09:04,880 --> 00:09:06,210
His daughter's abroad, though.

215
00:09:06,210 --> 00:09:07,920
She's only joining through video call.

216
00:09:10,090 --> 00:09:10,400
Yes.

217
00:09:15,120 --> 00:09:15,370
Yes.

218
00:09:19,120 --> 00:09:20,140
Oh, don't worry about it.

219
00:09:20,400 --> 00:09:21,760
It's nothing.

220
00:09:23,730 --> 00:09:25,690
You don't have to be so formal with me.

221
00:09:26,400 --> 00:09:27,280
Yes, we...

222
00:09:30,760 --> 00:09:31,800
I have to go.

223
00:09:31,800 --> 00:09:32,640
Bye.

224
00:09:36,210 --> 00:09:36,570
You...

225
00:09:37,210 --> 00:09:38,830
I'll throw these away. You take a break.

226
00:09:40,400 --> 00:09:42,370
"It's nothing."

227
00:09:43,250 --> 00:09:44,820
"You don't have to be
so formal with me."

228
00:09:46,210 --> 00:09:47,210
It was too loud in there.

229
00:09:47,280 --> 00:09:49,040
I came out for some peace and quiet.

230
00:09:49,970 --> 00:09:50,760
Peace and quiet.

231
00:09:52,400 --> 00:09:54,050
You just came out to get away from me.

232
00:09:55,520 --> 00:09:56,090
To call

233
00:09:56,090 --> 00:09:58,040
your "sweetheart" behind my back.

234
00:09:59,970 --> 00:10:02,450
You're being unreasonable.
You should be nicer to me.

235
00:10:02,760 --> 00:10:03,520
Why should I?

236
00:10:03,520 --> 00:10:04,990
You think you're some hot commodity?

237
00:10:05,640 --> 00:10:06,880
Why should I pander to you?

238
00:10:07,570 --> 00:10:08,530
Let me make this clear.

239
00:10:08,550 --> 00:10:10,369
There are a bunch
of well-educated gentlemen

240
00:10:10,370 --> 00:10:11,570
inside that auditorium.

241
00:10:11,760 --> 00:10:12,970
I can talk to them instead.

242
00:10:13,120 --> 00:10:14,490
Go on. Carry on with your call.

243
00:10:14,610 --> 00:10:15,920
- Go on.
- Fine. Forget about it.

244
00:10:15,920 --> 00:10:17,520
No... you...

245
00:10:20,210 --> 00:10:20,800
You're done?

246
00:10:23,800 --> 00:10:24,520
Listen.

247
00:10:26,370 --> 00:10:27,520
That fairy will be here soon.

248
00:10:27,730 --> 00:10:28,730
It's time.

249
00:10:28,730 --> 00:10:30,090
Wait for her by the entrance.

250
00:10:30,090 --> 00:10:30,330
I...

251
00:10:30,370 --> 00:10:32,640
Go get her and bring her here.
Let me know when she's here.

252
00:10:32,730 --> 00:10:33,860
But I don't know who she is!

253
00:10:36,330 --> 00:10:38,450
She's a 60-year-old lady!

254
00:10:39,040 --> 00:10:39,760
Skinny.

255
00:10:40,640 --> 00:10:41,930
Wobbles a little when she walks.

256
00:10:42,490 --> 00:10:44,090
If you really can't be sure,

257
00:10:44,090 --> 00:10:45,040
send me a photo of her.

258
00:10:45,040 --> 00:10:46,090
I know her.

259
00:10:46,280 --> 00:10:47,090
How do you know her?

260
00:10:51,120 --> 00:10:52,210
I'm her fairy.

261
00:10:52,490 --> 00:10:53,640
Stop asking questions!

262
00:10:53,690 --> 00:10:54,800
Just go!

263
00:10:54,850 --> 00:10:55,610
All right.

264
00:11:35,880 --> 00:11:37,610
Let's make sure we get the rhythm down.

265
00:11:37,760 --> 00:11:38,190
All right

266
00:11:39,640 --> 00:11:40,090
Rhythm.

267
00:11:40,400 --> 00:11:40,920
Oh.

268
00:11:41,730 --> 00:11:42,690
It's about time.

269
00:11:42,800 --> 00:11:43,970
I should go get Ms. Nie.

270
00:11:43,970 --> 00:11:45,879
What's the rush?
There's still half an hour to go.

271
00:11:45,880 --> 00:11:47,120
She might be here early.

272
00:11:47,850 --> 00:11:48,880
Fine. Go.

273
00:11:49,090 --> 00:11:50,120
Be careful. Don't rush.

274
00:11:53,000 --> 00:11:57,330
♪Oh, fair jasmine flower...♪

275
00:11:57,370 --> 00:12:01,250
♪Oh, fair jasmine flower...♪

276
00:12:03,490 --> 00:12:04,430
Where'd your grandpa go?

277
00:12:04,920 --> 00:12:06,370
No idea. He went backstage.

278
00:12:08,920 --> 00:12:10,919
I know. He's going to get Ms. Nie.

279
00:12:10,920 --> 00:12:15,450
♪I long to pluck one and wear it,♪

280
00:12:15,570 --> 00:12:18,640
♪but I fear it won't bloom next year.♪

281
00:12:19,280 --> 00:12:19,800
It's fine.

282
00:12:20,450 --> 00:12:21,970
Let's make sure you're at your best.

283
00:12:37,400 --> 00:12:38,519
Is that Mr. Shen over there?

284
00:12:38,520 --> 00:12:39,000
Yes.

285
00:12:39,280 --> 00:12:39,690
Come on.

286
00:12:40,730 --> 00:12:41,970
Mr. Shen.

287
00:12:41,970 --> 00:12:42,520
Hello.

288
00:12:42,520 --> 00:12:44,120
Mr. Shen, you look very handsome today.

